translated: Lindskog, Alarik Natanael, county director, lawyer, Västervik, b. June 19th, 1881 in Finnerödja, Skaraborg County. Son of the district provost Marcus L. and Hedda Grönvall. Married on the 13th of May with Sigrid Enéll. Education: Graduate of Skara 1900, preliminary examination in Uppsala 1903, higher court examination 1909. Judicial service in Tjust district court 1910-1912, assistant military auditor in Småland's regiment 1912, auditor 1915-1917, own law firm in Västervik 1912-1941, treasurer and director in Kalmar 1st Northern House Owners Association 1912-1940, secretary of Kalmar 1st Northern County Council from 1914, county director 1942-1946. Member of the church council 1924-1931, guardian from 1925, member of the police board from 1926, member of the church assembly from 1930, chairman of the police board from 1936, former member of the city council, vice-chairman of the board of Västerviks children's home from 1918, member of the board of St. Gertrud's hospital from 1929, vice-chairman from 1933, board member of the Scandinavian Bank's branch in Västervik from 1912, chairman from 1940, chairman of A-B Ankarsrums Bruk, A-B C. O. Ekblad & Co. and Café A-B Nornan. Member of the Freemasons, Odd Fellow, and SHT. Member of the Swedish Bar Association from 1918-1941. Recipient of Order of the North Star (RNO) and Order of Vasa (RVO).
